> Pesto is the secret ingredient in this recipe! It not only adds delicious flavor to
> the chicken, but also acts as the glue for a crunchy panko coating. Crispy
> roasted potatoes and a light green salad complete this easy weeknight dinner.

== Roasted Potatoes ==

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the #oven{} to 450 degrees.

Cut the @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch cubes.

Toss them on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil and a pinch of
@salt and @pepper. Place in the oven for ~{20-25%minutes}, tossing halfway
through cooking, until golden brown.

== Chicken ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup},
a drizzle of @olive oil, and a pinch of @salt and @pepper.

Place the @Chicken Breasts{12%ounce} on a lightly oiled baking sheet.

Spread the top of each chicken breast with 1 Tablespoon @Pesto{4%ounce}.

Press the panko mixture onto the top of the chicken to adhere.

Place in the oven for about ~{20%minutes}, until cooked through.

== Green Salad ==

Halve the @Lemon{1}.

In a #large bowl{}, toss together the @Mixed Greens{4%ounce}, a squeeze of
lemon juice, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{5%teaspoon}.

Season to taste with @salt and @pepper.

== Serve ==

Serve the mozzarella and pesto crusted chicken with the roasted potatoes and
green salad alongside. Enjoy!